                <mxCell id="68" value="4" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#2E73B8;strokeColor=none;fontColor=#FFFFFF;fontStyle=1;fontSize=14;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="1140" y="710" width="26" height="26" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="69" value="AWS service&#10;(Systems Manager)" style="sketch=0;outlineConnect=0;fontColor=#232F3E;gradientColor=none;fillColor=#E7157B;strokeColor=#ffffff;dashed=0;verticalLabelPosition=bottom;verticalAlign=top;align=center;html=1;fontSize=14;fontStyle=0;aspect=fixed;shape=mxgraph.aws4.resourceIcon;resIcon=mxgraph.aws4.systems_manager;shadow=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="1360" y="850" width="60" height="60" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="70" value="Privately to AWS service" style="endArrow=classic;html=1;strokeWidth=2.5;strokeColor=#8B0000;rounded=1;fontSize=14;fontColor=#8B0000;" edge="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry">
                        <mxPoint x="1100" y="880" as="sourcePoint"/>
                        <mxPoint x="1358" y="880" as="targetPoint"/>
                    </mxGeometry>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="71" value="5" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#2E73B8;strokeColor=none;fontColor=#FFFFFF;fontStyle=1;fontSize=14;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="1130" y="850" width="26" height="26" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="72" value="&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;Steps&lt;br&gt;(1) The workload performs a DNS lookup for the AWS service domain (for example ssm.{region}.amazonaws.com). The VPC Route 53 Resolver checks the associated Private Hosted Zone.&lt;br&gt;(2) Because PrivateDnsEnabled created the Lattice-managed PHZ on association, the resolver returns an IP address managed by VPC Lattice (not part of the VPC CIDRs).&lt;br&gt;(3) The client connects on TCP 443 to the VPC Lattice IP. The service network does not terminate TLS; it forwards the raw TCP flow to the Resource Configuration's resource gateway.&lt;br&gt;(4) The resource gateway performs a DNS lookup on the configured VPC endpoint domain (vpce-{id}.{service}.{region}.vpce.amazonaws.com) and forwards the traffic. The source IP seen by the endpoint is the resource gateway's.&lt;br&gt;(5) The interface VPC endpoint (PrivateLink) forwards the traffic privately to the AWS service. The response returns along the same path.&lt;/font&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FBFBFB;strokeColor=#879196;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=12;spacingTop=10;fontSize=14;fontColor=#232F3E;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="220" y="1039" width="1360" height="130" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
            </root>
        </mxGraphModel>
    </diagram>
</mxfile>